He faces charges of reckless driving and exceeding the speed limit. JOHANNESBURG Orlando Pirates player Happy Jele is expected to appear in court after being arrested for speeding on Monday morning.The sportsman was clocked travelling over 200 kilometres an hour in a 120 kilometre zone.He faces charges of reckless driving and exceeding the speed limit.Gauteng Community Safety spokesperson Busaphi Nxumalo said: The Pirates player was driving a 135i BMW travelling on the M1 near Sandton at an average speed of 223km per hour. He will appear in the Randburg Magistrate Court shortly. 